1.	Introduction

BIC USA, Inc., Distribution Center (BIC), a division of Societe BIC and BIC Corporation (herein referred to generically as "BIC Group") is committed to managing all operations in a manner that protects the environment, as well as the health and safety of employees, customers, and the public while fully complying with applicable laws and regulations. 

The purpose of this Risk Management Plan is to provide information about:  

1.	facility operations and the regulated substances handled;
2.	accidental release prevention and emergency response policies at the facility;
3.	general accidental release prevention program and chemical-specific prevention steps;
4.	the five-year accident history of the facility;
5.	the emergency response program; and
6.	planned changes to improve safety at the facility.

2.	Facility Operations and Regulated Substances Handled

BIC, located at 5900 Long Creek Park Drive in Charlotte, North Carolina, is a single occupant, 300,000 square feet, one to two-story warehouse and distribution facility for BiC products which are manufactured at BIC Group's and its third-party manufacturing facilities worldwide. No products are manufactured at this location.  The facility consists of a single building which contains warehouse operations, a quality laboratory, shipping/receiving docks, and office and meeting areas. 

In addition to various BiC finished consumer products, the facility handles several types of BiC lighters, all of which contain less than 5 grams of liquified isobutane gas per lighter. Isobutane is a regulated substance under the US EPA's Risk Management Program (RMP) with flammability similar to propane. The facility receives pallets of cartons of packaged lighters by truck/trailer and unloads them using forklifts. The lighters are already packaged, ready for shipment to retailers and consumers.  The number of lighters in each carton or pallet depends on the type of lighter, and the customers' demands for the size and ap
